c.log - a wrapper around console.log to cater for IE not being able to handle it.
console.log - sends messages to the console
invocations-invoking - calling a function
grunt - a javascript task runner
refactoring - making code simpler
assert - to throw an error if the expression passed into the function is false
functions - lines of code that we can reuse
pass function - passing a function in as a parameter in another function (craaaazy!)
comparissons - operators that are used to compare values, like >, <, and =.